<abstract><t>This document defines a new DNS OPCODE for DNS Stateful Operations (DSO).  DSO messages communicate operations within persistent stateful sessions, using type-length-value (TLV) syntax.  Three TLVs are defined that manage session timeouts, termination, and encryption padding, and a framework is defined for extensions to enable new stateful operations.</t></abstract>

